ars at the time was kanata. so there was THAT &quot;HOLY FUCK WE’RE DOOMED&quot; feeling too, knowing this means kanata is FOR SURE going to be the 5* of the ryuseitai reminiscence. i remember trying to predict when ryuseitai reminiscence could happen PURELY through how long ago kanata’s last 5* was LOL. event story thoughts translation of chiaki’s scenes in crossroad can be found here, in case re-reading them helps envision the fandom’s reaction back then! AND THEN, I FINALLY UNLOCKED THE STORY AMIDST MY MINDBLOWN BRAIN AND SHAKINGS HANDS, AND STARTED TO LIVETWEET IT. i tried to get a translation out asap BECAUSE HOOOLY SHIT CHIAKI’S SCENES WERE CRAZY. HE WAS SO MEEK AND SCARED WHILE BEING MADE FUN OF BUT HE WAS STILL TRYING TO BE A HERO!? HE TRIED TO SAVE A TIED-UP EICHI?! THIS IS RELEVANT TO THE CROSSROAD PLOT BECAUSE HE INADVERTENTLY RUINED KEITO’S PLAN BY DOING THIS…!?!? CHIAKI USED TO CALL THE OTHER 3RD YEARS BY &quot;-KUN&quot;!? KURO AND CHIAKI FRIENDSHIP!??!?!? KURO AND CHIAKI WERE THE NERD BEFRIENDS DELINQUENT TROPE!?!?!? this is the 3rd reminiscence in the same year, so fans were fueled even more that SURELY, SURELY RYUSEITAI IS SOON?! AFTER ALL THESE BUILDING BLOCKS WERE ADDED IN THE SAME YEAR…?? little did we know they had WAAAAY more in mind for us than just that (like, we didn’t even know about how kanata was seen as a living god by his household yet, that was revealed a whole month later. WE DIDN’T EVEN KNOW ABOUT JIN HAVING RELATIONS TO RYUSEITAI JUST YET EITHER!!!!). little did we know that chiaki wearing glasses wasn’t even a thing of the past. that he actually STILL wears them… and we only found out about THAT part months later in sweet halloween, another insane event for chiaki’s lore!! but gosh i remember so many fans, me included, feeling both shocked and pleasantly surprised by the story reveal, but also so sad for him because he Did Not Seem Okay. there’s the obvious one where he was mocked on stage, but his last chapter in crossroad gave really worrying signs of someone desperate to be a hero and struggling in an environment that’s constantly against him. so a lot of crossroad chiaki fanworks were either meek glasses chiaki trying his best but clearly scared, or sometimes much more desolate like him being bullied. meanwhile, him legitimately being A Megane Boy Who Was Made Fun Of made chiaki’s classic &quot;SHUT UP, FOUR EYES&quot; at akiomi in the main story even more ⁉ because wait a second… YOU were a megane too, though?! huh!? (little did we know, we were eventually going to learn that chiaki has a complex about his glasses self and it actually makes perfect sense… 😊) the theories and meta were FLOOOODINGGGG my twitter TL throughout the event period. sadly i don’t remember much of it anymore, and i can’t find them either, but based on my reaction tweets back then, people were likely linking 2nd year chiaki back to all the hints we got so far (like how chiaki said he got sick of the color red at one point), as well as talking about how far he’s come based on climax, supernova, etc. but most of all, &quot;oh god, are we really ready for ryuseitai reminiscence???&quot; like okay we knew chiaki was depressed, we knew he cried a lot in the past, but… possible bullying!?!? he was a nerd!? like, it was really shocking but exciting to see the hints we had known thus far come to life in an ACTUAL 2nd year chiaki scene, while still not knowing much about ryuseitai’s reminiscence yet. it took until gang came out in 2018 for us to find out JUST HOW HORRIBLE HIS SITUATION WAS BACK THEN. HE WAS LEGITIMATELY BULLIED BY RYUSEITAI MEMBERS???? WHAT???? while crossroad does mention that the ryuseitai members weren’t Good Students, it was still mostly fan speculation that he could have been bullied by them. before gang came out, most of us were still under the impression that it’s mostly just the delinquents who looked down on him, not his own unit members… random tangent about the fandom, but tsumugi’s birthday happened in the middle of the crossroad event, and his birthday somehow broke the servers and it took a WHILE for it to be fixed. i don’t 100% remember anymore what the bugs were, but it was practically impossible to play his birthday campaign and i think the crossroad event too. fans could barely celebrate the poor guy’s birthday. so that was also mixed in as a new historical event for the fandom too LMAO but yeah, for crossroad chiaki, there were just… SOOOO many fanworks of connecting 2nd year chiaki to his present (3rd year) self, happy with ryuseitai!! getting what he wanted! so much focus on how his &quot;it’ll be okay!&quot; sounded so weak and fearful… so much on how he tried to be a hero no matter how scared he was… the resurgence of theories about eichi and chiaki’s possible relationship (i talk about that here)… some people just straight up feeling so horribly sad about his crossroad scenes that they instead drew nerd chiaki being cute and happy keep in mind crossroad WAS IN THE SAME YEAR AS CLIMAX, THE RYUSEITAI REPAYMENT FESTIVAL STORY. AND THE SAME YEAR AS ALL THESE OTHER INSANE EMOTIONAL ROLLERCOASTERS ENSTARS THREW AT THE FANDOM. AND NOT TO MENTION!!! RYUSEITAI 3RD CD WAS JUST AROUND THE CORNER TOO SO IT WAS AN INSANE WEEK FOR A RYUSEITAIP!! in retrospect, 2017 was truly fucking insane in so many ways omg… like megane chiaki was IN LATE JULY. we still had the rest of the year for whatever else they were planning to throw at us. and god, did they throw A Lot on just ryuseitaiP alone. to conclude… it was truly a monumental moment. who would’ve fucking thought crossroad would be where chiakiP get to be fed. the fact it still took another 2 years for us to get ryuseitai reminiscence after all those reveals makes it even crazier… they really made us sit on all those random hints and small reveals of past chiaki until we finally got The Story. kanata’s appearance reveal took all the way until meteor impact too, so even though fans knew chiaki was a megane by now, fanworks depicting past chiaki and kanata still had kanata looking the same as he did in his 3rd year. which is interesting, because it means you can actually pinpoint when a past kanata &amp; chiaki fanwork must’ve been drawn based on their appearances alone LOL this was really long, but i had to break down every layer of what it meant to wake up on july 31st to megane chiaki. genuinely crazy and chaotic and unpredictable. and now i can’t imagine an enstars without megane chiaki, hehe 😊💞 i hope this was a fun read, and i badly hope megane chiaki makes his comeback in !! era eventually, because i just know it would break the fandom all over again… it’s been so long since his last megane card (since 2019…) thank you for asking, it was so much fun to go down a nostalgia trip and really remind myself how Important that moment was for chiakiP!! if you’re interested in more fandom history, i’m slowly compiling all my answers in the fandom history category ❤️

If ryuseitai had a sekai what do you think it would be like? I’ve been wondering it since the prsk collab and I was thinking maybe it would be a city sekai? Or something like that idrk

Sent and answered in June 2025. tweet link of the answer

this ask summoned back the proseka collab i’m crying /lh
i really like the idea of a city for their sekai!! especially since most tokusatsus happen in cities and towns, and cities tend to be the &quot;melting pot&quot;, which suits ryuseitai having diverse personalities 😊💞
but i’m sorry, anon… i have…. no thoughts of my own, i feel like you could share more about it than me 😭💔 i haven’t really dipped into proseka long enough to understand its world lore nor how sekai’s work and how they grow and develop… so i haven’t really thought up how a sekai would be for them.
but i asked if a fellow chiakiP would be fine with me sharing their vision, because i really liked it…. so here’s @/RenaiPro’s thoughts on ryuseitai’s sekai! capitalized chunks are from @/RenaiPro, the non-capitalized chunks are my random chip-ins.
&quot;From what I understand, while the person who created the Sekai has the most influence over it over time others who are part of it can end up influencing. So I love the idea of it originally being Chiaki’s, born out of both his desire to be and love of heroes as well as his loneliness and despair. Chiaki’s influences are very obvious at first. But as everyone else joins and as they slowly become a true unit and true friends you see everyone’s influences on the world.
Like it’s originally mostly Chiaki and tiny bits of Kanata. Kanata’s influences slowly growing over time as Ryuseitai becomes his family. As for the juniors, they originally have no influence but once their hearts truly accept Ryuseitai that’s when they start having influence on the Sekai. I also….really love the idea that Midori has no influence on the Sekai until the events of Repayfes….
A little mat you’d see in a dojo popping up for Tetora. A small pond with colorful fishes for Kanata. Midori having no influence adding to his insecurities in Repayfes because “see?! I don’t even influence in the Sekai like everyone else! That’s proof I’m not the same as everyone else!!!&quot; &quot;
&quot;as if it’s proof he should’ve left long ago like tetora said…💔 and the green ranger in the sekai means nothing to him he thinks anyone can replace and be that in his stead 💔&quot;
&quot;Chiaki telling Midori that this Sekai may have been born from Chiaki alone but it was Ryuseitai that nurtured it. It was all five of them together that has made it what it is now. And that while Midori may not SEE his influence on it, it’s still there all the same
And then…after Repayfes when Midori has finally fully devoted himself as a member of Ryuseitai…them going to the Sekai and Midori seeing an adorable little yuruchara plush waiting there…. The other fun thing is to imagine the Ryuseitai Sekai version of the vocaloid characters too since each Sekai gets their own individualized version!
From what I remember at their cores the Sekai versions of the vocaloids are the same, but their personalities are heavily influenced off the one(s) who created the Sekai. In this case going off the idea that the Sekai was born from Chiaki that would mean the vocaloids would all likely represent some aspect of Chiaki’s personality&quot;
&quot;DIBS ON BOOKWORM LEN (no)&quot;
&quot;Heck yeah little bookworm Len (give him glasses too)&quot;
and that’s about all i have to share…! i think it would definitely be so fun and interesting, ryuseitai’s so full of color and personality that there’d be so much to explore!! if you have any thoughts feel free to share, considering we’re about to get proseka x enstars part 2 (global edition)💞
